				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Keeping aggro... <a name="40358"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 17 04 6:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Bards never keep aggro well, but it can be done with the help of all in the group. I have tanked the Commander camps many times to help folks get their emperor keys in SSRA. I just make sure I am the puller and slower. Then I hit the mob with two DOTS with a drum equipped and then switch out the drum and hit the mob. That will usually hold aggro for almost all of the fight. Make sure to refresh the DOTS so that they don't drop and most mobs will keep whacking you.
<br />

<br />
Another technique is to have a someone root the mob. Then, you will have aggro if you are the closest to the mob.
<br />

<br />
Barring that you can buy a BOC or a SOD I guess.
<br />

<br />
Drumm
<br />
65 Bard of Torv
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
