				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">edit: Ok, I must be having a brain fart or something. I would swear black and blue that a warrior friend linked me a BoC only recently, and it showed warrior only. Just what did he link me then </span></blockquote> 
<br />

<br />
A BoC *can* be warrior only if the put an anger augment in it. Since that augment is warrior only the usable class will read only as warrior.
<br />

<br />
We lose in snap aggro. As someone pointed out we can build it over time, which is fine I guess, but then a group is waiting on you to get aggro before they can do anything and even that aggro may or may not be enough to hold someone from stealing it somewhat easily.
<br />

<br />
Do not waste your money on a SoD. The proc on that is a 0 second DD stun (288 damage). A copper hammer or striking should give you just as much aggro at 1% of the cost since that procs force shock (179 DD 0 sec stun). For a bard you will see the same aggro generated by either one really.
<br />

<br />
Maybe a copper hammer with a yakesha (sp) augment in it for more stunning? </span></td>
